00:00:22,083 --> 00:00:24,583
of Black Vinegar Middle
School, started to take on

8
00:00:24,666 --> 00:00:26,708
a life of their own.

9
00:00:26,791 --> 00:00:28,666
"White T Poison"...

10
00:00:28,750 --> 00:00:30,208
This was the title given to Mob,

11
00:00:30,291 --> 00:00:33,416
whose identity had
yet to be revealed.

12
00:00:35,625 --> 00:00:38,166
[FUJI]
White T Poison...

13
00:00:38,250 --> 00:00:39,708
I'll be the one to defeat him!

14
00:00:39,791 --> 00:00:41,375
[MISO GANG gasps]

15
00:00:42,583 --> 00:00:43,958
I'm gonna defeat this Poison guy

16
00:00:44,041 --> 00:00:46,583
and make him admit
that I'm the best.

17
00:00:46,666 --> 00:00:49,583
So the next target
is Salt Middle School.

18
00:00:49,666 --> 00:00:52,541
White T Poison will
make excellent prey.

19
00:00:52,625 --> 00:00:54,833
This is my chance to shine.

20
00:00:54,916 --> 00:00:57,000
[NARRATOR]
And so, the rumor mill continued

21
00:00:57,083 --> 00:00:58,666
churning out of control.

22
00:00:58,750 --> 00:01:00,416
The fierce battle to see
who would take down

23
00:01:00,500 --> 00:01:03,666
White T Poison was
about to begin.

24
00:02:38,916 --> 00:02:40,916
Whew! Thanks for the help!

25
00:02:41,000 --> 00:02:42,791
Somehow I managed
to make it back

26
00:02:42,875 --> 00:02:46,083
from the particle
level all by myself.

27
00:02:46,166 --> 00:02:47,875
But my spiritual
energy was way less

28
00:02:47,958 --> 00:02:49,416
than it used to be.

29
00:02:49,500 --> 00:02:51,833
So I couldn't get back
into the house anymore.

30
00:02:51,916 --> 00:02:54,083
It appears that
low-level spirits

31
00:02:54,166 --> 00:02:55,541
can't go anywhere
near this place

32
00:02:55,625 --> 00:02:58,666
simply because
Shigeo lives here.

33
00:02:58,750 --> 00:03:00,250
[RITSU]
What is that?

34
00:03:00,333 --> 00:03:03,541
Some kinda talking
jellyfish-looking thing?

35
00:03:04,666 --> 00:03:07,416
I know what needs to be done.

36
00:03:07,500 --> 00:03:09,916
[DIMPLE]
Huh? Wanna shake hands?

37
00:03:10,000 --> 00:03:11,166
[RITSU]
I have to exorcise it!

38
00:03:11,250 --> 00:03:12,958
[DIMPLE]
Whoa, wait a second!

39
00:03:13,041 --> 00:03:14,625
Stop kneeing me
in the face already!

40
00:03:14,708 --> 00:03:16,875
I'm not a threat!
I'm Shigeo's friend!

41
00:03:16,958 --> 00:03:17,916
You're what?

42
00:03:18,000 --> 00:03:19,458
You could even
call me his mentor.

43
00:03:19,541 --> 00:03:20,916
I'll let you off
the hook this time,

44
00:03:21,000 --> 00:03:22,916
because you were obviously
confused and panicked.

45
00:03:23,000 --> 00:03:24,541
But, that aside...

46
00:03:24,625 --> 00:03:26,375
I've got a proposition.

47
00:03:26,458 --> 00:03:28,083
How about you and I team up?

48
00:03:28,166 --> 00:03:29,000
No thanks.

49
00:03:29,083 --> 00:03:30,500
Hey, let's not be so hasty.

50
00:03:30,583 --> 00:03:32,416
Wait a second, just hear me out.

51
00:03:32,500 --> 00:03:35,333
You've only recently awakened
your psychic powers, right?

52
00:03:35,416 --> 00:03:38,916
[RITSU gasps]
What? I have psychic powers now?

53
00:03:39,000 --> 00:03:40,583
The fact that you
can see me is proof

54
00:03:40,666 --> 00:03:42,875
of your newfound abilities.

55
00:03:42,958 --> 00:03:44,041
The name's Dimple.

56
00:03:44,125 --> 00:03:45,916
I'm what most people
would call a ghost.

57
00:03:46,000 --> 00:03:47,958
So are my psychic powers
only strong enough

58
00:03:48,041 --> 00:03:50,000
to allow me to see
ghosts like you?

59
00:03:50,083 --> 00:03:51,708
[DIMPLE]
Well, I see you haven't realized

60
00:03:51,791 --> 00:03:54,541
how to use them, yet.

61
00:03:54,625 --> 00:03:56,125
Go ahead.

62
00:03:56,208 --> 00:03:59,041
You should be able to do that
now, just like your brother.

63
00:03:59,125 --> 00:04:00,916
[RITSU]
I shouldn't get my hopes up.

64
00:04:03,708 --> 00:04:05,958
[DIMPLE]
Hm? What's the matter?

65
00:04:06,041 --> 00:04:10,333
[RITSU] Doing anything like
this is way out of my reach.

66
00:04:10,416 --> 00:04:11,416
[DIMPLE]
What's with him?

67
00:04:11,500 --> 00:04:13,375
Does he have a
complex or something?

68
00:04:13,458 --> 00:04:14,875
Well, that's understandable,

69
00:04:14,958 --> 00:04:17,083
given who his
brother is and all.

70
00:04:17,166 --> 00:04:22,333
[RITSU]
It... It's... It's not...

71
00:04:22,416 --> 00:04:25,125
I can't do it!

72
00:04:25,208 --> 00:04:27,041
Dimple!

73
00:04:27,125 --> 00:04:29,125
It's not bending!

74
00:04:29,208 --> 00:04:31,958
Hey, relax, kid.

75
00:04:32,041 --> 00:04:33,541
[RITSU]
What the--?

76
00:04:33,625 --> 00:04:35,291
Did I do that?

77
00:04:37,541 --> 00:04:39,416
[DIMPLE]
Join me, little Ritsu...

78
00:04:39,500 --> 00:04:42,208
Join me and I'll help you
surpass your brother.

79
00:04:42,291 --> 00:04:44,458
[RITSU gasps]

80
00:04:44,541 --> 00:04:48,166
[RITSU]
Surpass... my brother?

81
00:04:48,250 --> 00:04:50,833
Is that even possible?

82
00:04:51,875 --> 00:04:56,000
[RITSU] I can be more
powerful... than Shige?

83
00:04:56,083 --> 00:04:59,250
Sure you can if you'll
let me use your body.

84
00:05:00,875 --> 00:05:02,458
Ritsu's not eating with us?

85
00:05:02,541 --> 00:05:04,583
I guess he's not hungry.

86
00:05:04,666 --> 00:05:07,375
I wonder what could
be wrong with him.

87
00:05:07,458 --> 00:05:09,125
Is he upset about something?

88
00:05:09,208 --> 00:05:10,041
[MOB'S MOM]
No...

89
00:05:10,125 --> 00:05:12,958
In fact, he seems oddly happy.

90
00:05:14,000 --> 00:05:15,208
[RITSU] How do I get
to the point where I can

91
00:05:15,291 --> 00:05:17,208
use my powers freely?

92
00:05:17,291 --> 00:05:18,666
It's better to
actually try them out,

93
00:05:18,750 --> 00:05:20,416
rather than explain,
little Ritsu.

94
00:05:20,500 --> 00:05:21,791
Stop calling me that.

95
00:05:21,875 --> 00:05:24,333
Fine, then. Plain
old Ritsu it is.

96
00:05:24,416 --> 00:05:25,875
Now, how 'bout you
close your eyes,

97
00:05:25,958 --> 00:05:27,875
and relax your entire body.

98
00:05:31,166 --> 00:05:33,833
[DIMPLE] Prepare for
possession, you fool!

99
00:05:33,916 --> 00:05:36,666
Now your body's mine
for the taking!

100
00:05:38,500 --> 00:05:39,750
[DIMPLE]
Heh, heh!

101
00:05:39,833 --> 00:05:40,958
What?!

102
00:05:41,041 --> 00:05:44,083
I've possessed him,
but I can't control him?

103
00:05:44,166 --> 00:05:46,666
Hey, Dimple. Where'd you go?

104
00:05:46,750 --> 00:05:48,125
[DIMPLE] It's because
my spiritual powers

105
00:05:48,208 --> 00:05:50,666
have become so weak... Damn it!

106
00:05:54,875 --> 00:05:55,958
[shcool bell rings]

107
00:05:56,041 --> 00:05:57,083
[STUDENT 7A]
I heard the student council

108
00:05:57,166 --> 00:05:58,666
took care of the problem.

109
00:05:58,750 --> 00:06:00,416
[STUDENT 7B] You mean with
the pervy gang leader?

110
00:06:00,500 --> 00:06:01,875
[STUDENT 7C]
Wow, way to go.

111
00:06:01,958 --> 00:06:04,791
[STUDENT 7D] They're the
heroes of the school.

112
00:06:04,875 --> 00:06:07,375
[SHINJI]
Yamazaki, Year 2, Class 4.

113
00:06:07,458 --> 00:06:08,958
I'd like a word with you.

114
00:06:09,041 --> 00:06:10,833
Huh? What do you want?

115
00:06:10,916 --> 00:06:12,791
[SHINJI]
Your coat. It isn't buttoned.

116
00:06:12,875 --> 00:06:15,833
[YAMAZAKI]
So what? Buzz off.

117
00:06:15,916 --> 00:06:17,875
I can do it.

118
00:06:17,958 --> 00:06:20,625
Now, I can use psychic
powers, Dimple.

119
00:06:20,708 --> 00:06:22,166
[DIMPLE]
That's because I'm helping

120
00:06:22,250 --> 00:06:23,708
to regulate their output.

121
00:06:23,791 --> 00:06:25,583
But rest assured,
these abilities

122
00:06:25,666 --> 00:06:28,416
have always been
there, lying dormant.

123
00:06:28,500 --> 00:06:29,833
And it's my guess
that the reason

124
00:06:29,916 --> 00:06:31,958
they came out now is
due to some radical

125
00:06:32,041 --> 00:06:34,875
change in your emotional state.

126
00:06:34,958 --> 00:06:36,916
Have you endured some
"way-above-average"

127
00:06:37,000 --> 00:06:38,750
stress levels lately?

128
00:06:38,833 --> 00:06:40,458
Like pooping your
pants in public,

129
00:06:40,541 --> 00:06:44,041
or getting caught peeking
into the girls' locker room?

130
00:06:44,125 --> 00:06:45,458
What kind of a question is that?

131
00:06:45,541 --> 00:06:46,791
I'd never do those things.

132
00:06:46,875 --> 00:06:47,875
I was joking, Ritsu.

133
00:06:47,958 --> 00:06:51,166
Don't be so damn serious. Oh...

134
00:06:51,250 --> 00:06:52,208
That's right.

135
00:06:52,291 --> 00:06:54,458
You're an honor
student, aren't ya?

136
00:06:54,541 --> 00:06:57,958
Then, what is it?
Did you do something bad?

137
00:06:58,041 --> 00:06:59,166
[SHINJI]
A rumor's going around that

138
00:06:59,250 --> 00:07:01,583
you're stealing the
girls' gym clothes.

139
00:07:01,666 --> 00:07:03,833
Huh? The hell are
you talkin' about?

140
00:07:03,916 --> 00:07:06,333
[SHINJI] The student council
did some investigating.

141
00:07:06,416 --> 00:07:08,333
And what'd we find
out, Kageyama?

142
00:07:08,416 --> 00:07:10,625
We discovered some of
the girl's gym clothes

143
00:07:10,708 --> 00:07:13,250
tucked away and
hidden in your bag.

144
00:07:13,333 --> 00:07:15,916
What?! You guys are lyin'!

145
00:07:16,000 --> 00:07:17,583
[SHINJI]
Deny it if you want,

146
00:07:17,666 --> 00:07:20,208
but that may not
go so well for you.

147
00:07:20,291 --> 00:07:22,416
You see, the school's
been very strict

148
00:07:22,500 --> 00:07:24,166
with deviants lately.

149
00:07:25,333 --> 00:07:28,541
[SHINJI] But I'm here to
offer you a way out of this.

150
00:07:28,625 --> 00:07:32,666
Simply admit Onigawara
ordered you to do these things.

151
00:07:32,750 --> 00:07:36,791
If you comply, you're
merely another victim.

152
00:07:36,875 --> 00:07:39,291
Sound good? Now button up.

153
00:07:40,583 --> 00:07:42,083
[NARRATOR] Using these
and other similar methods,

154
00:07:42,166 --> 00:07:43,750
the whole school was cleaned up,

155
00:07:43,833 --> 00:07:47,625
turning it into the optimal
environment for academics.

156
00:07:47,708 --> 00:07:49,708
However, because
of the considerably

157
00:07:49,791 --> 00:07:52,000
immoral strategy that
was used upon certain

158
00:07:52,083 --> 00:07:54,625
delinquent students to
accomplish this outcome,

159
00:07:54,708 --> 00:07:56,666
a deep scar would
be forever engraved

160
00:07:56,750 --> 00:07:58,666
on their lives.

161
00:07:58,750 --> 00:08:00,291
And the two student
council members

162
00:08:00,375 --> 00:08:03,916
saddled with this task had
to live with that burden.

163
00:08:04,000 --> 00:08:05,833
So they either became
drunk with power,

164
00:08:05,916 --> 00:08:08,666
feeling a delusional sense
of accomplishment,

165
00:08:08,750 --> 00:08:11,208
or they suffered greatly.

166
00:08:12,791 --> 00:08:13,916
[DIMPLE]
Whoa!

167
00:08:14,000 --> 00:08:16,833
Ritsu, your power's
grown even more!

168
00:08:16,916 --> 00:08:19,375
[RITSU]
I see, corruption and guilt...

169
00:08:19,458 --> 00:08:20,958
Those are the things
that become fuel

170
00:08:21,041 --> 00:08:23,000
for my powers.

171
00:08:23,083 --> 00:08:25,041
Whatever you're doing,
it is working!

172
00:08:25,125 --> 00:08:25,750
What's the matter?

173
00:08:25,833 --> 00:08:27,833
Something eating at you?

174
00:08:27,916 --> 00:08:30,875
[RITSU] Dimple, you just
won't stop talking.

175
00:08:30,958 --> 00:08:31,458
Oh?

176
00:08:31,541 --> 00:08:32,625
[RITSU]
Tell me.

177
00:08:32,708 --> 00:08:34,833
If I could control my
powers on my own,

178
00:08:34,916 --> 00:08:37,583
would I be able to
make you disappear?

179
00:08:37,666 --> 00:08:40,500
[DIMPLE] Wait, is his
personality changing, too?

180
00:08:46,000 --> 00:08:47,958
Whoa! S-Seriously?

181
00:08:48,041 --> 00:08:51,250
Amazing... That's
incredible, Kageyama!

182
00:08:51,333 --> 00:08:52,750
Want me to keep going?

183
00:08:52,833 --> 00:08:54,333
If you'd like to see
a bigger example,

184
00:08:54,416 --> 00:08:55,750
I could fold your car in half.

185
00:08:55,833 --> 00:08:57,666
[MITSUURA]
What?!

186
00:08:57,750 --> 00:08:59,875
[MITSUURA] What in the
hell's gotten into him??

187
00:09:04,083 --> 00:09:05,541
[sighs]

188
00:09:05,625 --> 00:09:06,708
Excuse me...

189
00:09:06,791 --> 00:09:08,500
May I help you with something?

190
00:09:08,583 --> 00:09:10,125
I heard from Kamuro
that you're the one

191
00:09:10,208 --> 00:09:12,875
who's been planting all
that false evidence around.

192
00:09:12,958 --> 00:09:15,291
Tell me, are you the
one who framed us?

193
00:09:15,375 --> 00:09:17,791
I have no idea what
you're talking about.

194
00:09:17,875 --> 00:09:18,458
Dimple.

195
00:09:18,541 --> 00:09:19,500
Leave it to me.

196
00:09:19,583 --> 00:09:21,541
Even if I did do such a thing...

197
00:09:22,958 --> 00:09:24,125
Now it's too late.

198
00:09:24,208 --> 00:09:24,958
[grunts]

199
00:09:25,041 --> 00:09:26,041
Why, you little...

200
00:09:26,125 --> 00:09:28,583
Who in the hell do
ya think we are?!

201
00:09:28,666 --> 00:09:29,791
[growls]

202
00:09:29,875 --> 00:09:33,500
[gasps, screams]

203
00:09:36,250 --> 00:09:38,416
That does it! Get him!

204
00:09:38,500 --> 00:09:39,833
You're dead meat!

205
00:09:43,500 --> 00:09:47,416
[chuckles]

206
00:09:47,500 --> 00:09:48,333
[GIRL 7A]
A fight.

207
00:09:48,416 --> 00:09:49,875
[GIRL 7B]
Scary!

208
00:09:49,958 --> 00:09:51,291
[GIRL 7A] But isn't that guy's
hair, like, totally amazing?

209
00:09:51,375 --> 00:09:52,166
Check it out!

210
00:09:52,250 --> 00:09:53,208
[GIRL 7B]
You're right!

211
00:09:53,291 --> 00:09:54,250
[GIRL 7C]
Whoa!

212
00:09:55,958 --> 00:09:57,541
[TERU]
Hey, you there.

213
00:09:59,583 --> 00:10:00,666
What's up?

214
00:10:00,750 --> 00:10:02,333
[DIMPLE]
Gah! That's...

215
00:10:02,416 --> 00:10:03,833
I think you've done enough.

216
00:10:06,083 --> 00:10:08,916
If you depend on that,
you'll get hurt.

217
00:10:09,000 --> 00:10:11,208
You've got the wrong
idea about this.

218
00:10:11,291 --> 00:10:12,083
I know...

219
00:10:12,166 --> 00:10:13,500
You think you're really special.

220
00:10:13,583 --> 00:10:15,291
It's hard looking at
someone who reminds me

221
00:10:15,375 --> 00:10:17,833
of the way I used to be.

222
00:10:17,916 --> 00:10:19,958
Consider this a warning.

223
00:10:20,041 --> 00:10:22,625
Don't try to live relying
on psychic powers.

224
00:10:22,708 --> 00:10:24,333
[RITSU gasps]

225
00:10:24,416 --> 00:10:26,333
Are you another esper like me?

226
00:10:26,416 --> 00:10:28,875
I have no idea who you are...

227
00:10:28,958 --> 00:10:31,750
...but I have no need to
take warnings from you.

228
00:10:31,833 --> 00:10:33,500
Don't mess with this guy!

229
00:10:33,583 --> 00:10:35,125
He's not someone you can beat!

230
00:10:35,208 --> 00:10:36,250
[RITSU]
I'm sure he's not much different

231
00:10:36,333 --> 00:10:38,541
from the people at
the Awakening Lab.

232
00:10:38,625 --> 00:10:41,125
I wanna size up our powers.

233
00:10:41,208 --> 00:10:42,583
[DIMPLE]
Ritsu?! You idiot!

234
00:10:42,666 --> 00:10:44,041
Don't do it!

235
00:10:44,125 --> 00:10:45,291
[gasps]

236
00:10:45,375 --> 00:10:47,375
[TERU] Why, thank you
for the handshake.

237
00:10:47,458 --> 00:10:51,291
I'm Teruki Hanazawa. Pleasure.

238
00:10:51,375 --> 00:10:52,416
Don't try to fight him!

239
00:10:52,500 --> 00:10:53,458
Let go! Now!

240
00:10:53,541 --> 00:10:56,000
Having trouble
standing, are you?

241
00:10:56,083 --> 00:10:58,041
You're so young.

242
00:10:58,125 --> 00:10:59,416
[GIRLS scream]

243
00:11:04,625 --> 00:11:06,500
Now's your chance! Run for it!

244
00:11:06,583 --> 00:11:10,625
[RITSU panting]

245
00:11:10,708 --> 00:11:12,541
[RITSU] I was surprised
at how strong he was,

246
00:11:12,625 --> 00:11:14,000
back there.

247
00:11:14,083 --> 00:11:16,416
Maybe it's 'cause his
brain's so developed.

248
00:11:16,500 --> 00:11:18,791
Could that coincide
with his power level?

249
00:11:18,875 --> 00:11:19,875
No.

250
00:11:19,958 --> 00:11:21,583
His brain's not huge--
that was a wig.

251
00:11:21,666 --> 00:11:23,875
Though I'm not sure
why he was wearing it.

252
00:11:23,958 --> 00:11:25,458
[RITSU]
I'm so frustrated.

253
00:11:25,541 --> 00:11:28,666
How could I lose to someone
other than my brother?

