00:11:28,750 --> 00:11:32,708
Dimple. I wanna
get even stronger.

255
00:11:32,791 --> 00:11:35,375
So I won't lose to
anyone ever again.

256
00:11:37,708 --> 00:11:39,500
[WOMAN 7A]
Little boy.

257
00:11:39,583 --> 00:11:41,541
Do you have a moment?

258
00:11:43,458 --> 00:11:44,666
Huh?

259
00:11:51,625 --> 00:11:54,041
[WOMAN 7A]
This is the Vase of Happiness.

260
00:11:54,125 --> 00:11:55,916
A renowned potter put his heart

261
00:11:56,000 --> 00:11:58,500
and soul into making
it a one of a kind.

262
00:11:58,583 --> 00:12:02,000
Anyone who buys this item
will surely be blessed.

263
00:12:02,083 --> 00:12:04,791
Now it normally goes
for about 2.5 million yen,

264
00:12:04,875 --> 00:12:07,916
but I'll make you a deal:
800,000 yen just for you.

265
00:12:08,000 --> 00:12:09,458
I don't have that kind of money.

266
00:12:09,541 --> 00:12:12,083
Then I'll drop the
price to 500,000.

267
00:12:12,166 --> 00:12:14,583
[MOB] Well, I don't have
500,000 yen, either.

268
00:12:14,666 --> 00:12:15,750
Running low on funds?

269
00:12:15,833 --> 00:12:18,666
Just call your
mommy and ask her.

270
00:12:18,750 --> 00:12:21,458
I'm pretty sure my mom
also wouldn't buy it.

271
00:12:21,541 --> 00:12:23,500
[WOMAN 7A]
This isn't over yet, kid.

272
00:12:23,583 --> 00:12:25,541
[WOMAN 7A]
Hey, why don't you touch it?

273
00:12:25,625 --> 00:12:28,125
The grainy texture
feels so nice.

274
00:12:28,208 --> 00:12:30,500
--Here.
--[MOB] Er, I can't really tell.

275
00:12:30,583 --> 00:12:32,916
[gasps]

276
00:12:33,000 --> 00:12:34,166
[MOB]
That was close.

277
00:12:34,250 --> 00:12:35,416
[WOMAN 7A]
How did he--?

278
00:12:36,958 --> 00:12:38,541
[WOMAN 7A]
You should be careful.

279
00:12:41,041 --> 00:12:42,125
Hey, you broke it.

280
00:12:42,208 --> 00:12:43,291
[gasps]

281
00:12:43,375 --> 00:12:44,791
Wait! I-I didn't--!

282
00:12:44,875 --> 00:12:46,833
[WOMAN 7A] What? You're going
to say it was my fault?

283
00:12:46,916 --> 00:12:48,250
[MOB]
Uh-- No, but...

284
00:12:48,333 --> 00:12:49,833
[WOMAN 7A]
Look, little boy...

285
00:12:49,916 --> 00:12:51,416
Problems that you can
solve with money

286
00:12:51,500 --> 00:12:53,166
are better than those
that you can't.

287
00:12:53,250 --> 00:12:54,541
Got it?

288
00:12:54,625 --> 00:12:58,416
Oh, what a run of bad luck.
Did you break that, sir?

289
00:12:58,500 --> 00:13:00,541
Do you have a phone?

290
00:13:00,625 --> 00:13:01,541
I-I don't...

291
00:13:01,625 --> 00:13:02,166
[phone rings]

292
00:13:02,250 --> 00:13:03,250
[MOB gasps]

293
00:13:03,333 --> 00:13:05,000
[MAN 7A]
That rang at the perfect time.

294
00:13:05,083 --> 00:13:06,666
Why don't you answer it?

295
00:13:08,000 --> 00:13:09,833
[ARATAKA]
Now what are you doing, Mob?

296
00:13:09,916 --> 00:13:11,541
Why'd you make me
come down here, anyway?

297
00:13:11,625 --> 00:13:13,458
You know I'm taking
a meeting soon.

298
00:13:14,583 --> 00:13:17,291
Would you happen to be
this boy's guardian, sir?

299
00:13:17,375 --> 00:13:18,500
Oh, I get it.

300
00:13:18,583 --> 00:13:20,833
[MAN 07A] It's 5,000,000
yen to replace this.

301
00:13:20,916 --> 00:13:23,833
You mean that huge
piece of junk?

302
00:13:23,916 --> 00:13:25,000
No way it's worth that.

303
00:13:25,083 --> 00:13:26,958
Wait... What'd you say?

304
00:13:27,041 --> 00:13:29,625
Listen, you don't seem
to know how things work.

305
00:13:29,708 --> 00:13:31,458
Maybe I'll teach you a lesson.

306
00:13:31,541 --> 00:13:32,666
[ARATAKA]
Ow! Ow! Ow!

307
00:13:32,750 --> 00:13:34,750
You totally cracked my clavicle.

308
00:13:34,833 --> 00:13:37,666
That's gonna cost
you, my friend.

309
00:13:37,750 --> 00:13:39,041
[MAN 7A]
Huh?

310
00:13:39,125 --> 00:13:42,791
The hospital will fix me up
for about a million yen.

311
00:13:42,875 --> 00:13:45,916
You can't be serious, you
dumbass! That's outrageous!

312
00:13:46,000 --> 00:13:48,166
[ARATAKA] Verbal abuse causes
psychological damage.

313
00:13:48,250 --> 00:13:50,375
So, that's gonna
be another million.

314
00:13:50,458 --> 00:13:51,083
Listen, you!

315
00:13:51,166 --> 00:13:52,208
You've got bad breath.

316
00:13:52,291 --> 00:13:54,125
Subjecting me to
it's another million.

317
00:13:54,208 --> 00:13:55,375
[MAN 07A]
What the hell?!

318
00:13:55,458 --> 00:13:56,500
[ARATAKA] Your voice is
causing me ear damage.

319
00:13:56,583 --> 00:13:58,166
That'll be another million.

320
00:13:58,250 --> 00:14:00,916
Look. You frayed my shirt.

321
00:14:01,000 --> 00:14:03,916
Then, that's one more million
for garment damage.

322
00:14:04,000 --> 00:14:05,583
Now, that's equal
to what he owes you

323
00:14:05,666 --> 00:14:06,875
for the vase.

324
00:14:06,958 --> 00:14:08,500
I'm no stranger to
the kind of business

325
00:14:08,583 --> 00:14:09,666
you guys are running.

326
00:14:09,750 --> 00:14:11,333
Come on, Mob. Let's go.

327
00:14:11,416 --> 00:14:12,708
You're not goin' anywhere.

328
00:14:12,791 --> 00:14:14,083
There's no escape!

329
00:14:14,166 --> 00:14:15,916
This boy's misfortune
was decided

330
00:14:16,000 --> 00:14:17,958
the moment he broke
the Vase of Happiness.

331
00:14:18,041 --> 00:14:20,583
I'd hate for anything
bad to happen to him!

332
00:14:20,666 --> 00:14:23,458
[ARATAKA]
"Misfortune"? "Bad things"?

333
00:14:23,541 --> 00:14:25,041
Before I came here,
I was talking

334
00:14:25,125 --> 00:14:28,166
to someone who'd been
haunted by an evil spirit.

335
00:14:28,250 --> 00:14:29,708
Apparently, it can
be passed along,

336
00:14:29,791 --> 00:14:32,375
and now the spirit's
haunting me.

337
00:14:32,458 --> 00:14:34,166
I hear strange noises at night,

338
00:14:34,250 --> 00:14:36,166
weird things keep
popping up in pictures,

339
00:14:36,250 --> 00:14:37,791
doors open and
shut on their own.

340
00:14:37,875 --> 00:14:39,458
It becomes unbearable.

341
00:14:39,541 --> 00:14:40,875
Who knows?

342
00:14:40,958 --> 00:14:43,083
The spirit might have
transferred to you guys by now.

343
00:14:43,166 --> 00:14:45,541
Be careful when you
go to bed tonight.

344
00:14:45,625 --> 00:14:47,125
Huh? A haunting?

345
00:14:47,208 --> 00:14:49,083
Doesn't feel too great, does it?

346
00:14:49,166 --> 00:14:52,416
That's pretty much exactly
what you guys are doing.

347
00:14:52,500 --> 00:14:54,416
[BOTH laugh]

348
00:14:54,500 --> 00:14:55,500
A ghost?

349
00:14:55,583 --> 00:14:57,875
What are you, a
little kid? So scary!

350
00:14:58,916 --> 00:15:00,666
[WOMAN 7A, MAN 7A gasp]

351
00:15:00,750 --> 00:15:02,750
[BOTH shriek]

352
00:15:02,833 --> 00:15:05,291
[BOTH whimpering]

353
00:15:05,375 --> 00:15:07,625
[BOTH scream]

354
00:15:08,708 --> 00:15:11,375
[ARATAKA] That sure
shut those two up quick.

355
00:15:11,458 --> 00:15:12,375
And I gotta say...

356
00:15:12,458 --> 00:15:14,750
That last bit was great, Mob.

357
00:15:14,833 --> 00:15:16,083
Huh?

358
00:15:16,166 --> 00:15:18,041
You shook the building
to scare them, didn't ya?

359
00:15:18,125 --> 00:15:19,375
Nu-uh.

360
00:15:19,458 --> 00:15:21,125
I thought all that was you
sending the evil spirit

361
00:15:21,208 --> 00:15:22,583
after those two.

362
00:15:22,666 --> 00:15:23,583
Wait a second.

363
00:15:23,666 --> 00:15:24,375
Are you saying you
couldn't see--?

364
00:15:24,458 --> 00:15:25,833
[ARATAKA]
Come on.

365
00:15:25,916 --> 00:15:28,500
Of course I could see it.

366
00:15:28,583 --> 00:15:29,791
I can't believe them.

367
00:15:29,875 --> 00:15:31,708
Con artists are
terrible people.

368
00:15:31,791 --> 00:15:33,791
The worst of the worst.

369
00:15:33,875 --> 00:15:35,208
You said it.

370
00:15:35,291 --> 00:15:37,375
Only the lowest of the
low try to take advantage

371
00:15:37,458 --> 00:15:40,916
of someone's weakness and
exploit it for their own gain.

372
00:15:41,000 --> 00:15:43,041
[TOKUGAWA]
What? You as well?

373
00:15:43,125 --> 00:15:44,041
Yes.

374
00:15:44,125 --> 00:15:45,583
He said, "So, you're
trash, too?"

375
00:15:45,666 --> 00:15:49,166
And all I was doing was
chewing some gum during class.

376
00:15:49,250 --> 00:15:53,541
[TOKUGAWA] Kamuro, this school
doesn't belong to you.

377
00:15:53,625 --> 00:15:56,000
We still have other pieces
of trash to deal with.

378
00:15:56,083 --> 00:15:57,541
Let's keep things moving.

379
00:15:57,625 --> 00:15:59,291
[RITSU]
You plan to continue this?

380
00:15:59,375 --> 00:16:01,416
[SHINJI]
Come on.

381
00:16:01,500 --> 00:16:03,791
You're not going to
suggest we stop, are you?

382
00:16:03,875 --> 00:16:05,041
[RITSU] No.

383
00:16:05,125 --> 00:16:07,458
It just that you make me
feel sick, that's all.

384
00:16:07,541 --> 00:16:10,250
You get off on
this, don't you?

385
00:16:10,333 --> 00:16:11,583
[SHINJI chuckles]

386
00:16:11,666 --> 00:16:14,416
I was correct in choosing
you as an accomplice.

387
00:16:14,500 --> 00:16:17,333
If you knew, why did
you decide to help me?

388
00:16:18,583 --> 00:16:20,875
[RITSU]
Because I was tired.

389
00:16:20,958 --> 00:16:22,708
Just tired of being myself.

390
00:16:22,791 --> 00:16:25,458
Of everything. Maybe
I wanted to find out

391
00:16:25,541 --> 00:16:28,416
what it would feel
like to be a fool.

392
00:16:28,500 --> 00:16:30,583
There's more to it than that.

393
00:16:30,666 --> 00:16:33,041
In the end, it made
us both popular.

394
00:16:33,125 --> 00:16:34,541
You and I have
become the heroes

395
00:16:34,625 --> 00:16:36,791
of this entire school.

396
00:16:36,875 --> 00:16:38,291
So "looks-too-old-
for-school-guy"

397
00:16:38,375 --> 00:16:39,916
wanted to be popular?

398
00:16:41,666 --> 00:16:43,125
[RITSU] I, on the other
hand, have obtained

399
00:16:43,208 --> 00:16:45,875
a much bigger world.

400
00:16:45,958 --> 00:16:47,125
By the way, President,

401
00:16:47,208 --> 00:16:49,166
did you happen to find
any telepaths out there?

402
00:16:49,250 --> 00:16:51,666
If I did, I wouldn't
be here now, would I?

403
00:16:51,750 --> 00:16:52,875
Inukawa!

404
00:16:52,958 --> 00:16:54,583
You can't put a bomb there!
That's cheating!

405
00:16:54,666 --> 00:16:57,708
Kurata, would you mind being
a little quieter, please?

406
00:16:57,791 --> 00:17:00,625
'Cause I've still got a few more
things I wanna say over here.

407
00:17:00,708 --> 00:17:02,125
[TOME]
Oh. Sorry.

408
00:17:02,208 --> 00:17:04,125
[ONIGAWARA]
Musashi, that's enough.

409
00:17:04,208 --> 00:17:06,291
[MUSASHI]
No, it's not! Now, man up!

410
00:17:06,375 --> 00:17:08,291
Go to class, Onigawara!

411
00:17:08,375 --> 00:17:10,333
I've got no place there.

412
00:17:10,416 --> 00:17:13,458
I mean, none of my friends
will even talk to me anymore.

413
00:17:13,541 --> 00:17:14,125
[door scrapes]

414
00:17:14,208 --> 00:17:15,000
Oh, a visitor.

415
00:17:15,083 --> 00:17:15,875
[yelps]

416
00:17:15,958 --> 00:17:17,375
The student council president!

417
00:17:17,458 --> 00:17:19,416
I see this place is
as rotten as the rumors

418
00:17:19,500 --> 00:17:22,458
led me to believe.
More to the point...

419
00:17:22,541 --> 00:17:25,541
What are you doing
on campus, Onigawara?

420
00:17:25,625 --> 00:17:26,916
Infiltrating the school when you

421
00:17:27,000 --> 00:17:28,208
haven't been showing
up to class?

422
00:17:28,291 --> 00:17:29,125
[ONIGAWARA]
No!

423
00:17:29,208 --> 00:17:30,291
But I can't stay at home!

424
00:17:30,375 --> 00:17:32,000
If I do, my mom will
ask me why I'm not--

425
00:17:32,083 --> 00:17:33,583
[MUSASHI]
Listen to me, President.

426
00:17:33,666 --> 00:17:35,875
Onigawara didn't do
what you think he did.

427
00:17:35,958 --> 00:17:38,708
Should I have you all dealt with
for being his accomplices?

428
00:17:38,791 --> 00:17:40,958
'Cause, don't forget,
I have the power to do so.

429
00:17:41,041 --> 00:17:42,833
--[MUSASHI] What?!
--[STUDENT 7D] President...

430
00:17:42,916 --> 00:17:44,791
President, some weird guy just
showed up at the school gates.

431
00:17:44,875 --> 00:17:46,166
What should we do?

432
00:17:46,250 --> 00:17:47,291
It never ends.

433
00:17:47,375 --> 00:17:50,625
The problems pile up
one after another.

434
00:17:50,708 --> 00:17:52,083
So who are you guys?

435
00:17:52,166 --> 00:17:55,291
I told the other nerd that
I'm here for White T Poison!

436
00:17:55,375 --> 00:17:57,791
"White T Poison"?
What on earth is that?

437
00:17:57,875 --> 00:17:58,958
[KENZAKI]
Don't play dumb!

438
00:17:59,041 --> 00:18:01,041
He's the talk of all
the thugs right now.

439
00:18:01,125 --> 00:18:02,750
I'll deal with him, President.

440
00:18:02,833 --> 00:18:04,375
That should settle things.

441
00:18:04,458 --> 00:18:05,958
[KENZAKI groans]

442
00:18:06,041 --> 00:18:08,541
[SHINJI]
Whoa! You really laid him out!

443
00:18:08,625 --> 00:18:11,250
[RITSU]
It was done in self defense.

444
00:18:11,333 --> 00:18:12,541
Not to mention,
they were students

445
00:18:12,625 --> 00:18:15,875
from another school,
so it shouldn't matter.

446
00:18:15,958 --> 00:18:18,333
[SHINJI] Not only is he
willing to get into a fight,

447
00:18:18,416 --> 00:18:21,000
he's incredibly strong, too.

448
00:18:21,083 --> 00:18:22,166
[GANG MAN 7A]
Hey...

449
00:18:22,250 --> 00:18:24,166
Are you the guy that
knocked out Kenzaki?

450
00:18:24,250 --> 00:18:25,250
Huh?

451
00:18:25,333 --> 00:18:27,291
Who's better known
as White T Poison?

452
00:18:27,375 --> 00:18:29,458
Wh-What are you--

453
00:18:29,541 --> 00:18:30,958
I was just watching, I didn't--!

454
00:18:31,041 --> 00:18:33,333
[GANG MAN 7A] Then who the
hell <i>is</i> White T Poison?!

455
00:18:33,416 --> 00:18:34,375
I don't--

456
00:18:38,291 --> 00:18:40,958
That's enough!
It's time to stop this!

457
00:18:41,041 --> 00:18:42,375
Man, you look awful.

458
00:18:42,458 --> 00:18:43,666
[SHINJI]
This is all your fault!

459
00:18:43,750 --> 00:18:45,625
I became a victim
because of you!

460
00:18:45,708 --> 00:18:48,416
You taught a gang leader from
another school a lesson!

461
00:18:48,500 --> 00:18:49,541
Don't you understand?!

462
00:18:49,625 --> 00:18:51,708
If that's true, then so be it.

463
00:18:51,791 --> 00:18:53,833
He got what was coming to him.

464
00:18:55,583 --> 00:18:57,500
Y-You're kidding me!

465
00:18:57,583 --> 00:18:58,958
No! Not again!

466
00:18:59,041 --> 00:19:01,458
Are you that White T Poison guy?

467
00:19:01,541 --> 00:19:03,625
[SHINJI whimpering]

468
00:19:03,708 --> 00:19:06,541
[SHINJI screams]

469
00:19:07,583 --> 00:19:09,583
[SHINJI'S DAD]
Oh, it's you, Tokugawa.

470
00:19:09,666 --> 00:19:13,041
Shinji doesn't wanna
see anyone right now.

471
00:19:13,125 --> 00:19:14,583
Is that so?

472
00:19:15,750 --> 00:19:17,083
[RITSU]
Disgusting.

473
00:19:17,166 --> 00:19:18,958
For someone who wanted
to get rid of the garbage,

474
00:19:19,041 --> 00:19:20,916
you should've started
with your own room.

475
00:19:21,000 --> 00:19:22,583
[SHINJI gasps]

476
00:19:22,666 --> 00:19:24,916
[SHINJI]
H-How did you get in here?

477
00:19:25,000 --> 00:19:26,416
No matter.

478
00:19:26,500 --> 00:19:28,416
Either way, we still have trash
to contend with at school.

479
00:19:28,500 --> 00:19:29,583
No way!

480
00:19:29,666 --> 00:19:32,000
I'm done with all of that!
Get out of here!

481
00:19:32,083 --> 00:19:33,083
It's too late.

482
00:19:33,166 --> 00:19:34,791
We've both done
something unforgivable

483
00:19:34,875 --> 00:19:36,000
with our roles in this.

484
00:19:36,083 --> 00:19:38,333
No one's going to
save us, understand?

485
00:19:38,416 --> 00:19:43,083
[whimpering]

486
00:19:44,250 --> 00:19:45,958
[RITSU] It seems the
puppet's been broken.

487
00:19:46,041 --> 00:19:48,250
The school is finally clean.

488
00:19:48,333 --> 00:19:49,958
[DIMPLE]
So now whatcha gonna do?

489
00:19:50,041 --> 00:19:51,291
Ya know thugs from
the other schools

490
00:19:51,375 --> 00:19:53,041
are gonna keep showin' up.

491
00:19:53,125 --> 00:19:55,833
With these powers, I can
do whatever I want.

492
00:19:55,916 --> 00:19:56,833
Yeah!

493
00:19:56,916 --> 00:19:58,833
You could be a
psychic superstar!

494
00:19:58,916 --> 00:20:00,041
Dimple...

495
00:20:00,125 --> 00:20:02,375
You're trying to use me
as well, aren't you?

496
00:20:02,458 --> 00:20:03,416
[DIMPLE]
Huh?!

497
00:20:03,500 --> 00:20:04,458
What are you
talking about, Ritsu?

498
00:20:04,541 --> 00:20:06,708
We're partners!
I'm on your side!

499
00:20:16,708 --> 00:20:18,541
Oh, here they come.

500
00:20:18,625 --> 00:20:20,291
More than usual today.

501
00:20:22,416 --> 00:20:25,833
[TERU] I came to see what was
going on and, of course...

502
00:20:25,916 --> 00:20:29,916
Are you that White T Poison guy
who beat Hanazawa and Kenzaki?

503
